sentences.english: The survivors wandered about the jungle for days before being picked up by a search party.

sentences.english: Each rive has its upward, middle and backward part.

sentences.english: The middle stretch of the Yangtze is a natural transportation and communications nexus.

sentences.english: Fetal DNA in maternal plasma could be regarded as the gene resource for noninvasive prenatal diagnosis.

sentences.english: Fung is the origin of the Yangtze River middle reaches, stone house culture river phoenix.

sentences.english: There are at least nine physiographic cycles in the middle reaches of the Yellow River during the Late Cenozoic Era.

sentences.english: The migration of this period has some characteristics, which infected the social development of the region.

sentences.english: The grass swimming fish and shrimp, let the ducks grew fat and strong.

sentences.english: It is the ravening lion roaming the earth seeking whom it may devour.

sentences.english: The influence in the upper reaches is larger than the lower stream.

sentences.english: Midstream means the transportation of new oil by ship routes and pipelines.
